<h1 style="background-image:url(http://www.flowplayer.org/img/title/streaminge.png)">
	Flash plugin: <strong>shareembed</strong>
	<em>Video sharing plugin</em>
</h1>


<h2>Introduction</h2>

<p>
    
    The Video Share plugin is used to share video links via email, social networking sites, and embed the code directly into a website. Most viral video sharing
    functions out there are javascript based, relying on javascript API's which is an issue embedding a video into a site that strips out javascript like Myspace. 
    Being a flash based plugin this works around this issue, and therefore video link sharing, embedding and emailing can continue regardless of these limitations imposed by these sites. 
</p>

<p>
	<small>(Version <strong>3.1.4</strong>)</small>
</p>

<h2>Features</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
		Video embed code function without relying on javascript API's. 
  </li>
  <li>
		Video sharing link function to various social networking sites.  
  </li>
  <li>
		Video link emailing to friends using either a server-side email system or locally using the end users email client.
  </li>
  <li>
        Token based authentication support, to protect the server-side email system from spammers.
  </li>
  <li>
        Video link support to the following social networkingt sites:
        
        <ul>
            <li>Facebook</li>
            <li>Myspace</li>
            <li>Twitter</li>
            <li>Bebo</li>
            <li>Orkut</li>
            <li>Digg</li>
            <li>Stumbleupon</li>
            <li>Livespaces</li>
        </ul>
  </li>
</ul>



<h2>Configuration With Email Script and Token Script</h2>

<p>
    Here we can configure email sharing with a server-side email system with support for a token based authentication system enabled with the <samp>emailScriptURL</samp> config property. 
    The token here is requested from a specified script url using the <samp>emailScriptTokenURL</samp>
</p>

<p>
    The config property <samp>emailSubject</samp> is required here along with the config property <samp>shareTitle</samp> which is used as the title for the link in the email message determined by the email template. 
    The config property <samp>emailTemplate</samp> is used to determine how the email message is formatted. 
</p>

<p>
    Enabled by default, the email, embed and share link icon buttons can be enabled / disabled using the <samp>enableEmail</samp>, <samp>enableEmbed</samp> and <samp>enableShare</samp> config properties.
</p>

