<a name="email_script_system"></a>
<h2>Email Script System</h2>

<p>
	The email script system handles the server-side emailing of the email share function. <br><br>
	  
    The email function if configured will send a token to this script for authentication using the "token" post variable. <br><br>
	  
    The token script if requested and configured is required to return a token in JSON format like {"token": "3435952382509853908250925"} <br><br>
	  
    The script is required to handle the following post variables. <br><br>
    
    <ul>
	  <li>name - The sender's name (required)</li>
	  <li>email - The sender's email (required)</li>
	  <li>subject - The email subject (required)</li>
	  <li>message - The email message (required)</li>
	  <li>to - A comma delimitered list of emails to send to (required)</li>
	  <li>token - The token to authenticate before allowing to email (optional)</li>
	  </ul>
	  
	  NOTE: It is advisable to filter the post variables for email headers, as well as run spam checks. <br><br> 
	  
	  The emailing system supplied in the source provides an example for filtering and validating input and running spam checks against the akismet and typepad spam services. 
</p>


